1. create folder ==> MVC
2. create npm init
3. npm install packages => express, mongoose, body-parser, dotenv,cors,...etc
4. create .env file
5. create app.js
            ==> require express
            ==> app.use bodyparser
            ==> app.use router
6. create server.js
        ====> import app,connect mongodb, app.listen server, dotenv
        ====> update "start": "node server" in package.json file for npm start
7. create models folder and then create required schema
8. create controller folder and add require function for get post,update, delete method
9. create views folder and create required template files
10. create middleware folder where we can handle authorization and validations
12. create Router folder based on the controller
13. import router in the app js folder and add api in the url , ==> app.use('api/user/', userRouter)
